"{\n  \"correct\": \"no\",\n  \"explanation\": \"The method set_xticks() expects the tick positions to be in the same format as the x-axis data, which in this case are datetime objects. However, set_xticks() is being passed the unique dates from the DataFrame, which are datetime objects, so this part is correct. The issue lies with set_xticklabels(), which expects the labels to be strings, but it is being passed datetime objects. Additionally, the labels should be formatted to match the DateFormatter format.\",\n  \"patch\": \"19,20c19,20\\n< ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n< ax.set_xticklabels(labels=df.date.unique(), rotation=45)\\n---\\n> ax.set_xticks(df.date.unique())\\n> ax.set_xticklabels(labels=[d.strftime('%Y-%m') for d in df.date.unique()], rotation=45)\\n\"\n}"